exports[`golden listing > selected output is stable for examples/99-bottles.mkpro 1`] = `
"## Listing
# Setup Listing
 Step | Code | Command                 | Comment
------+------+-------------------------+----------------
   -- |   -  | enter bottles           | enter any value 0..99 in X
   00 |  40  | X→П 0                   | setup bottles
   01 |  50  | С/П                     | setup complete

# Main Listing
 Step | Code  | Command                 | Comment
------+-------+-------------------------+----------------
   00 | 60    | П→X 0                   | text display verse
   01 | 01 00 | 10                      | text tens divisor
   03 | 13    | ÷                       | text tens
   04 | 34    | К [x]                   | text tens integer
   05 | 41    | X→П 1                   | text tens scratch
   06 | 0F    | F Вx                    | text ones from last X
   07 | 35    | К {x}                   | text ones fraction
   08 | 01 00 | 10                      | text ones scale
   10 | 12    | ×                       | text ones
   11 | 42    | X→П 2                   | text ones scratch
   12 | 01 01 | 11                      | text display tens prefix
   14 | 48    | X→П 8                   | text display prefix scratch
   15 | 01 02 | 12                      | text display tens offset
   17 | 47    | X→П 7                   | text display digit offset
   18 | 62    | П→X 2                   | text display ones digit
   19 | 53    | ПП                      | text digit renderer
   20 | 34    | 34                      | text digit renderer
   21 | 4A    | X→П a                   | text display rendered ones
   22 | 01 04 | 14                      | text display ones prefix
   24 | 48    | X→П 8                   | text display prefix scratch
   25 | 01 03 | 13                      | text display ones offset
   27 | 47    | X→П 7                   | text display digit offset
   28 | 61    | П→X 1                   | text display tens digit
   29 | 53    | ПП                      | text digit renderer
   30 | 34    | 34                      | text digit renderer
   31 | 6A    | П→X a                   | text display rendered ones
   32 | 0E    | В↑                      | show text
   33 | 50    | С/П                     | show text
   34 | 06    | 6                       | text digit renderer
   35 | 11    | −                       | text digit renderer
   36 | 0B    | /-/                     | text digit renderer
   37 | 5C    | F x<0                   | text digit renderer
   38 | 45    | 45                      | text digit renderer
   39 | 09    | 9                       | text digit complement
   40 | 10    | +                       | text digit complement
   41 | D7    | К П→X 7                 | text display byte
   42 | 10    | +                       | text display byte
   43 | 3A    | К ИНВ                   | text visible digit
   44 | 52    | В/О                     | text digit return
   45 | 01    | 1                       | text digit complement
   46 | 10    | +                       | text digit complement
   47 | D7    | К П→X 7                 | text display byte
   48 | 10    | +                       | text display byte
   49 | 3A    | К ИНВ                   | text visible digit
   50 | D8    | К П→X 8                 | text display prefix
   51 | 52    | В/О                     | text digit return

## Hex
00: 60 01 00 13 34 41 0F 35
08: 01 00 12 42 01 01 48 01
16: 02 47 62 53 34 4A 01 04
24: 48 01 03 47 61 53 34 6A
32: 0E 50 06 11 0B 5C 45 09
40: 10 D7 10 3A 52 01 10 D7
48: 10 3A D8 52

## Setup Program
40
50

## Explain
MK-Pro compile report
Steps: 52/999999
Delivery: hex
Optimizer: exact maximum
Reference: bolknote_99_bottles; span=53, entries=53, gaps=none, compiled=52, delta=-1, parity=smaller
Machine: mk61
Optimizer rules: automatic=yes; active=5, considered=0, candidates=55, planned=0
Budget: official=52, extra=0, physical=52
Intent IR: lowered=yes, v2=yes; intent=9, effects=52, cells=52

Preloads:
  bottles -> R0: stack.X (outside program cells)

Setup Program:
  Reason: initializes bottles
  00: 40 50

Registers:
  bottles: R0

Labels:
  ␀main: 00
  __loop_0: 00

Optimizations:
  - intent-domain-lowering: Lowered 1 state fields and 0 rules through the generic intent pipeline.
  - auto-preload-initial-state: Moved initial state into setup/preload values so official program cells stay focused on turn logic.
  - screen-text-lowering: Lowered screen __inline_show_13_0 as visible text "BEEr " plus bottles.
  - pre-shift-stack-lift: Removed 1 В↑ lift already supplied by a following stack-shifting command, made dead before a hard X2 overwrite, or made dead by a terminal halt sync.
  - dead-code-after-halt: Removed 1 unreachable op(s) from the entry CFG.
  - generated-setup-program: Generated optimized setup program for bottles.

Optimizer Capabilities:
  - store-recall-peephole: candidate; Elides immediate X->П r / П->X r pairs when the recall is not observable as the last X2 sync before context-sensitive ., /-/, or ВП restoration and its stack lift cannot reach a downstream stack consumer through stack-preserving ops or direct call/return continuations.
  - stack-current-x-scheduling: candidate; Keeps a just-computed value in X for a following expression, including commutative uses and one-shot temporaries.
  - tail-call-lowering: candidate; Replaces subroutine calls in tail position with direct jumps so rule factoring and terminal branches do not force extra returns or branch hops.
  - return-zero-jump: candidate; Uses В/О as one-cell БП 01 only when the return stack is known empty.
  - vo-return-body-reorder: candidate; Candidate: reorder HEAD/MAIN/SUB so a subroutine return lands at the program head and a ПП/В/О pair collapses. Single-use procedures are already inlined and tail-position calls already become direct jumps, so the remaining gain needs a global layout search with no proven safe trigger on the current programs.
  - super-number-deferred-normalization: candidate; Candidate: keep an un-normalized super-number (extra hidden mantissa digits) to defer a range/error check. The reference emulator models only the 8 visible mantissa digits, so the hidden-digit behavior the idiom relies on cannot be reproduced or safely proven, and no language construct produces it.
  - packed-position-type: candidate; Candidate: a language-level packed position type N.0000H carrying an integer position plus packed (hex) fractional sub-coordinates. The dual-use round-trip (К [x] recovers the position, К {x} recovers the packed fraction) is already exploited by constants-dual-use; a dedicated type would only add language surface that no current program consumes.
  - coord-list-scaled-decimal: candidate; Stores 10x10 board coordinates as y.x decimal values when all visible uses allow it, so row/column/diagonal scans avoid repeated /10 digit extraction.
  - dual-constant-sign-digit: candidate; Candidate: a language intent for a dual constant 1.|-00 plus compact sign-digits (2N..9N) and their comparison semantics. The negative-zero comparison behavior is already active through the negative-zero-threshold family; no current program needs the additional sign-digit literal surface.
  - branch-removal: candidate; Umbrella rule for replacing provably equivalent conditionals with branchless arithmetic, sign, extrema, or masked updates.
  - zero-condition-test: candidate; Uses direct F x?0 tests when one side of a condition is a proved zero, avoiding a zero literal and subtraction.
  - dispatch-compare-chain: candidate; Lowers high-level command dispatch automatically; small proven dispatches may use indirect or super-dark dispatch.

Machine Features Used:
  - code-data-overlay: Layout marked address cells as reusable code/data overlay candidates.; Address operands, constants, opcodes, and display bytes may share cells after conflict checks.
  - display-bytes: Display lowering marked cells as packed display-byte candidates.; Packed display bytes, hexadecimal mantissa digits, and sign-digit forms are available.
  - address-constants: Layout marked address cells as reusable constants.; Address cells may double as constants for indirect flow and data transforms.

Proofs:
  - return-stack-empty: not-needed; Program uses subroutine calls, so В/О-as-jump is not assumed globally.
  - value-ranges: proved; Collected source ranges for bottles.
  - observability: proved; Visible state is limited by display output: bottles.
  - display-byte-observable-boundary: assumed; Display-byte candidates are bounded by display output and the exact mk61 profile.

Cell Roles:
  00: 60 exec, display-byte - display byte role allowed
  12: 01 exec, display-byte - display byte role allowed
  13: 01 exec, display-byte - display byte role allowed
  14: 48 exec, display-byte - display byte role allowed
